Sentencas: A novel nanocomposite functional cathode material La0.54Sr0.40Fe0.20Co0.80O3-delta@Co0.01Ce0.79 Gd0.20O2-delta is synthesized by two-step autocombustion method for the use in solid oxide fuel cell in the temperature regime <= 800 degrees C.
Titulo: La0.54Sr0.4Fe0.2Co0.8O3-δ@Co0.01Ce0.79Gd0.2O2-δ functional cathode material for solid oxide fuel cell application

Sentencas: The calcined powder is characterized by XRD, UV-VIS, Raman spectroscopy and transmission electron microscopy for the evaluation of crystal structure, band gap, particle size and elemental distribution in support of such functional material.
Titulo: La0.54Sr0.4Fe0.2Co0.8O3-δ@Co0.01Ce0.79Gd0.2O2-δ functional cathode material for solid oxide fuel cell application

Sentencas: An interpenetrating network of LSFC surrounding the CoCGO phase is revealed by HAADF-STEM study.
Titulo: La0.54Sr0.4Fe0.2Co0.8O3-δ@Co0.01Ce0.79Gd0.2O2-δ functional cathode material for solid oxide fuel cell application

Sentencas: It exhibits high electrical conductivity (260 S cm(-1)) and low electrode polarization (0.05 Omega cm(2)) at 800 degrees C. Incorporating LSFC@CoCGO as cathode onto Ni-YSZ anode-supported cell using YSZ electrolyte and CoCGO as the buffer layer results high current density 2.88 A cm(-2) (at 0.7 V) at 800 degrees C and imparts excellent stability (<= 1%) at constant load of 0.5 A cm(-2) and 1 A cm(-2) upto 240 h.
Titulo: La0.54Sr0.4Fe0.2Co0.8O3-δ@Co0.01Ce0.79Gd0.2O2-δ functional cathode material for solid oxide fuel cell application

Sentencas: The stability of the performance is tried to correlate with the modified cathode materials.
Titulo: La0.54Sr0.4Fe0.2Co0.8O3-δ@Co0.01Ce0.79Gd0.2O2-δ functional cathode material for solid oxide fuel cell application
